	   <tr><td colspan=2>ok for all you 2hs wielding paladins, here is my current Dilemma:<br>The weapons i currently have in my possession are as follows:<br> - Mithril 2hs 21/32 after haste effect<br> - Ornate rune blade 19/30 lots stats<br> - Arbitors Great Combine Sword 30/43+15wis25mana<br> - Velium Battle Axe 30/40<br>I sold the velium Battle axe&nbsp;&nbsp;because i needed plat. If i sell the Arbitors, i will have enough to buy a FBSS. I cannot sell the Ornate as it is a guild weapon, I won on a roll , from a com raid i participated in, not to be sold.<br>I really want the FBSS so i want to sell the ARbitors to net me enough cash to buy one. <br>I feel that the Ornate Rune Blade with the FBSS is way better the the Arbitors without a FBSS?<br>What is yer slant on this diemma. <br>Should i have kept the Velium 30/40???<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloraim<br>Dwarf Paladin of the 45th Season.<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>ps. i really want a jade inlaid cresent axe as my dream weapon , until i can get the epic! its 32/40 with lots stats.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
