ight I Bought a DW Bracer for 2.5k , then went to solb to test it out ( Good ac at 16 , the stun takes too long to load to be of good use during a battle because i am not able to hit the mob while its loading, but great for pulling I think, still testing) but when i run back to bank to unload, a peep is selling a DW helm & bracer for 3k, so for 2.5k he will prob. sell both! Rats shoulda waited a few hours!<br>The market is really wierd, too, i waited 2 weeks to see a DW Bracer advertised, even when i auction WTB. last night 4 players answered my call. Talk about Feast or famine.<br>I think its all about being in the right place at the right time & knowledge of what an items real value range is. If you have a base level of plat.<br>there are some good opportunities out there. <br>Takes plat to make plat.<br>Hope this was helpful.<br>Tosk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>Dwarf Paladin of the 45th Season<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>ps. I know players that are addicted to just playing the market in EC, so be warned!<br>When solb is overcrowded & i do not have time to make the run to another location, i usually resign myself to auction my smithy wares & watch the auction closely. I often laugh to see some guy selling an item for 1k & see another player willing to pay 2k for it. They advertise, but do not watch the auction. Opportunity knocks.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
